📊 Statistical Quality Control Analysis
This project applies Statistical Quality Control (SQC) techniques to monitor and evaluate process stability using X̄ (X-Bar) Control Charts and R (Range) Control Charts. The analysis aims to determine whether the production process is statistically under control and to identify potential special-cause variations that may affect product quality.

Analysis Performed:
Processing quality data based on observation subgroups
Calculating sample means (X̄) and ranges (R)
Determining the Center Line (CL)
Calculating the Upper Control Limit (UCL)
Calculating the Lower Control Limit (LCL)
Constructing X̄ and R Control Charts
Evaluating process stability through control chart analysis
Interpreting quality control results
The analysis demonstrates how SQC can be used to assess whether a process remains within established control limits. By utilizing control charts, process variation can be monitored systematically, enabling early detection of quality issues and supporting continuous process improvement.

